   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "The `-avoidpartialspends` feature is normally disabled, as it may affect the optimal fee for payments. This PR tries the avoiding coin selector as well as the regular one in the case where users have `-avoidpartialspends` turned off, and uses the avoiding variant if its fee is less than or equal to the fee of the non-avoiding version.\r\n\r\n(The next step is to let users define a maximum fee that they are willing to pay in order to avoid partial spending; this is a specialization with `max_fee=0`.)\r\n\r\nPing @gmaxwell.",
